### Description

We are trying to create the **"Bahnschrift Light SemiCondensed"** font stream using the code below. However, the resulting font stream is Bahnschrift, which is a variable font containing multiple weights and widths, instead of the specific Bahnschrift Light SemiCondensed style. This is the issue we are encountering.

Platform: ASP.NET Core
Visual Studio version: 2022
.NET version : .NET 8.0
SkiaSharp version : 3.116.1


### Code


```cs
public void FontCreation()
{
   SKFontStyleWeight weight = SKFontStyleWeight.Light;
   SKFontStyleSlant sKFontStyleSlant = SKFontStyleSlant.Upright;
   SKFontStyleWidth sKFontStyleWidth = SKFontStyleWidth.SemiCondensed;
   SKTypeface typeface = SKTypeface.FromFamilyName(“Bahnschrift”, weight, sKFontStyleWidth, sKFontStyleSlant);
   SKStream skFontStream = typeface.OpenStream();
   if (skFontStream != null && skFontStream.Length > 0)
   {
       skFontStream.Rewind();
       const int bufferSize = 8192;
       byte[] buffer = new byte[bufferSize];
       int bytesRead;
       FileStream font = new FileStream(@"Font.ttf", FileMode.Create, FileAccess.Write);
       while ((bytesRead = skFontStream.Read(buffer, bufferSize)) > 0)
       {
           font.Write(buffer, 0, bytesRead);
       }
       font.Position = 0;
       font.Close();
   }

```


### Expected Behavior

This should return the Bahnschrift Light SemiCondensed font stream.

### Actual Behavior

This code is returning Bahnschrift font stream which is a variable font.

### Version of SkiaSharp

3.116.0 (Current)



